</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1694,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88">
Metasomal sternum 
<number box="[426,440,1767,1791]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" value="1.0">1</number>
with Y-shaped carina, stronger anterad, indistinct posterad. Tergum 
<number box="[1201,1215,1767,1791]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" value="1.0">1</number>
with deep, separate punctures. Tergum 
<number box="[366,380,1803,1827]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" value="2.0">2</number>
with elongate, slightly confluent punctures. Segments 
<number box="[993,1035,1802,1827]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
with fine, dense punctures, more or less confluent on sterna; sternum 
<number box="[555,569,1839,1863]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" value="2.0">2</number>
with sparse, separate ones. Pygidial area elongate, glabrous, impunctate, carinate laterally, weakly convergent posterad.
