<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1694,2007]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="17" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1982,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="88">Remarks.</emphasis>
The female of this new species is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen" authorityName="Chen" box="[886,1193,1982,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[886,1107,1982,2006]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="88">Hemutilla bifurcata</emphasis>
(Chen)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by having the clypeus posteriorly with a thin transverse carina (broad, flattened, V-shaped, strong ridge in 
<taxonomicName box="[1240,1377,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[1240,1377,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="89">H. bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the tergum 
<number box="[239,253,188,212]" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" value="1.0">1</number>
posteriorly with a tuft of golden setae (fringe of fuscous setae in 
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1156,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[1019,1156,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="89">H. bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the about same length bands of golden setae on terga 
<number box="[497,511,224,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[566,580,224,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" value="3.0">3</number>
(that on tergum 
<number box="[766,780,224,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" value="3.0">3</number>
much longer in 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1098,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[963,1098,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="89">H. bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
